<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-17801] RemoteLogManager may compute inaccurate upperBoundOffset for aborted txns</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-17801</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In RemoteLogManager.read, we compute startPos as the following.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
startPos = lookupPositionForOffset(remoteLogSegmentMetadata, offset);&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is the position returned by the offset index. The actual position for the first batch being read happens in the following, but startPos is not updated accordingly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
firstBatch = findFirstBatch(remoteLogInputStream, offset);&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We then use the inaccurate startPos to create fetchDataInfo.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
FetchDataInfo fetchDataInfo = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; FetchDataInfo(
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; LogOffsetMetadata(offset, remoteLogSegmentMetadata.startOffset(), startPos),
MemoryRecords.readableRecords(buffer));&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addAbortedTransactions(), we use startPos to find the upperBoundOffset to retrieve the aborted txns.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;long&lt;/span&gt; upperBoundOffset = offsetIndex.fetchUpperBoundOffset(startOffsetPosition, fetchSize)
.map(position -&amp;gt; position.offset).orElse(segmentMetadata.endOffset() + 1);&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The inaccurate startPos can lead to inaccurate upperBoundOffset, which leads to inaccurate aborted txns returned to the consumer.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
